About this item

  • 2024 Latest Ultra HD Display Technology: The fitness tracker for women and men is equipped with the latest ultra hd full touch color screen, delivering exceptional picture quality and highly responsive touch sensitivity, which brings you a unique visual and better interactive experience.With the companion app, there are more than 200 dial options for you to choose from and you could even customize the dial in your own style with your favorite photos
  • 24-Hours Health Monitoring: The health fitness watch adopts advanced sensors, which accurately monitors your blood oxygen, blood pressure and 24/7 heart rate. The fitness watches also track your sleep automatically and provide comprehensive sleep quality analysis with a sleep score and detailed information including the duration of light sleep,deep sleep, REM and awake time. You could check those real-time metrics anytime anywhere on your wrist and view recent seven days data records in the App
  • 128+ Exercise Modes and All-Day Activity Tracking: The activity tracker monitors your steps, distance, and calories burned all the day, so you can see how much progress you've made towards your fitness goals. During your exercise, the watch will track your data including real time heart rate, steps, calories burned, distance, and time of duration all the data will be sync to the App at the same time.It supports more than 128 exercise modes, including running, cycling, walking,yoga and so on
  • Mutiple Notifications and Reminders: With this smart watch fitness trackers for iPhone and android phones, you can receive notifications for incoming calls and read messages directly on your wrist even without taking out your phone. The smart fitness watches for women and men provide you with multiple health-related reminders including drinking water reminder, sedentary reminder, and women's menstrual period reminder, helping you to develop a healthier life style
  • Long Battery Life and IP68 Waterproof: Smart watches for women and men has multiple functions such as timer, stopwatch, alarm clock, find your phone, music control, weather forecast, dont disturb mode, brightness adjustment, camera control. With 1.5-2 hrs of charging, it supports 8-12 days of normal use and about 30 days of standby time. This smart watch is IP68 waterproof, ensuring worry-free use even while washing hands, engaging in sweaty activities

Product Description

The 2025 Latest Smart Fitness Watch: Your Everyday Health Companion and More!

Are you ready to elevate your lifestyle with cutting-edge technology, sleek design, and comprehensive health tracking? Meet this 2025 latest smart fitness watch, meticulously designed for todays tech-savvy and health-conscious individuals. This fitness tracker watch does so much more than just tell timeits your personal fitness coach, health tracker, communication hub, and lifestyle assistantall wrapped up into one powerful wearable device.

Whether youre hitting the gym, managing a busy workday, or just looking to stay healthier and more organized, this smartwatch will become an indispensable part of your daily life. And with its long battery life, waterproof design, and vast array of customizable features, its built to keep up with you every step of the way.

Stunning Visual and Operational Experience

Ultra HD Full Touch Color Screen

The moment you set eyes on the ultra-HD full touch color screen, youll realize this is no ordinary watch. With crystal-clear visuals, a vibrant color palette, and a smooth user interface, this smartwatch brings every interaction to life. Its high-resolution display ensures every swipe, tap, and notification is easy to read, whether youre indoors or out in bright sunlight.

More Than 200 Dial Options

Love personalization? Choose from more than 200 dial options! From classic and elegant to fun and modern, you can switch up the look of your watch to match your style, mood, or occasion. Youll never have to settle for one look again!

Comprehensive Health Tracking

24/7 Heart Rate Monitoring

Your heart is the center of your well-being, and this smartwatch monitors it continuously. With 24/7 heart rate monitoring, you can stay on top of your cardiovascular health no matter where life takes you. Whether you're resting, working out, or somewhere in between, this advanced heart rate sensor provides accurate, real-time insights into your heart's performance.

Blood Oxygen Monitoring

In todays fast-paced world, understanding your bodys oxygen levels is essential for maintaining overall wellness. The fitness tracker for women and men allows you to keep track of your blood oxygen saturation, an important indicator of your respiratory health. Perfect for athletes, mountain climbers, or anyone who wants to monitor their oxygen levels on-the-go!

Blood Pressure Monitoring

The blood pressure monitoring feature on the smart fitness watches helps you keep an eye on one of the most critical indicators of heart health. This functionality enables you to measure your blood pressure anytime, anywhere, giving you valuable insights into how your body reacts to daily activities.

Sleep Tracking

Waking up tired after a full night of sleep? The sleep tracker is here to help. By monitoring your sleep stageslight sleep, deep sleep, and REMthis feature provides you with detailed insights into your nightly rest. It helps you understand your sleep quality and offers recommendations on how to improve your overall sleep health. Start your days feeling refreshed, energized, and ready to conquer the world!

Stay Connected with Calls andMessages Notification

Stay in the loop, even when youre on the go. With calls and messages notifications, youll never miss an important call, text, or app notification again. Receive notifications from social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, and moreright on your wrist. Whether it's a quick glance at an incoming call or checking your messages discreetly during a meeting, this feature ensures that youre always connected without needing to constantly check your phone.

All-Day Activity Tracking and 128 Exercise Modes: Designed to Motivate You

Track Your Fitness Journey with 128 Exercise Modes

Whether you're a casual walker or an elite athlete, the 128 exercise modes tracking feature has something for everyone. This smartwatch is designed to accurately track a wide variety of exercises, from running and cycling to yoga, swimming, and strength training. Whatever your workout style, the fitness trackers adapt to your needs, giving you real-time data on your performance and helping you stay motivated.

Each activity is analyzed through advanced sensors, providing you with metrics such as calories burned, steps taken, distance traveled, and heart rate during the exercise. Sync your data with the App and watch yourself reach new fitness milestones!

All-Day Activity Tracking for a Healthier You

Even when youre not working out, this fitness watch works for you. With All-Day Activity Tracking, every step counts toward a healthier lifestyle. It tracks your steps, calories burned, distance covered, and active minutes throughout the day. You can set daily activity goals and watch your progress in real-time, pushing you to stay active and fit. Whether you're walking to work or taking a leisurely stroll in the park, this health activity tracker watch is there to keep you moving.

Mutiple Notifications and Reminders

Womens Health: Menstrual Period Reminder

For women, this heath fitness watch takes health tracking a step further with its Menstrual Period Reminder feature. It helps you track your menstrual cycle and provides helpful reminders for the different phases, ensuring you're always informed and prepared. This feature is a fantastic tool for women seeking to understand their bodies better and manage their health more effectively.

Drinking Water Reminder

Its easy to forget to drink water during a busy day or while focusing on work. But now, with the Drinking Water Reminder, your smartwatch ensures you stay hydrated. Set up reminders that prompt you to drink water at regular intervals, keeping your body hydrated and your energy levels high.

Sedentary Reminder

If youre sitting for too long, the sedentary reminder will nudge you to stand up, stretch, and move around. These gentle reminders help promote better posture, circulation, and overall well-being.

Your Daily Assistant: Multiple Functions to Simplify Your Life

Long Battery Life: Power Through Your Day

Theres nothing worse than your device dying halfway through the day. Thankfully, the long battery life of this smart watch ensures that you stay powered up for days on a single charge. With up to 7-12 days of battery life (depending on usage), you can enjoy uninterrupted access to all the features you love without constantly worrying about recharging. Now, you can focus on your day, not your charger.

IP68 Waterproof: Ready for Anything

Whether youre swimming, caught in the rain, or just washing your hands, you dont have to worry about damaging your fitness watch. Rated with IP68 waterproof protection, this smartwatch is designed to withstand the toughest conditions. Its built to be water-resistant and dustproof, allowing you to wear it with confidence in almost any situationwhether youre poolside or diving into a workout session.

Multiple Functions to Simplify Your Life

This fitness tracker watch is more than just a health and fitness tracker. With multiple functions, its your ultimate personal assistant. Enjoy features like a Timer, Stopwatch, Alarm Clock, and even a Find Your Phone option when your phone goes missing. Plus, you can control your music on-the-go with the Music Control feature, making it easy to switch tracks without reaching for your phone.

Stay ahead of the weather with the Weat her Forecast feature, and keep distractions at bay with Dont Disturb Mode, which lets you block unnecessary alerts whenever you need focus time. You can also adjust the screens brightness for the perfect view in any lighting condition and even use the Camera Control feature to snap hands-free photos.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars
Great for the price
I bought this watch to "upgrade", I gave my fitbit charge to my daughter. I was not sure this would fulfill my expectations. So far, it is.The watch itself is light and comfortable to wear, for me that is a big deal. The watch is waterproof also. All the different functions work great so far. I really like that I can customize the touchscreen with their different images or an image of my own. You can adjust the brightness of the screen even turn it into a flashlight. I am a very light sleeper, so I was curious about the sleep tracking function. It took me a little bit to actually leave the watch on my wrist while I sleep because I was afraid that the screen light would wake me up, it turns on every time you make a wrist motion. After reading the manual, I learned you can put the screen on DND mode through the app, which is also very easy to manage. Since it is synced with your phone, you can see the weather for today and the next 4 days, I don't need my husband to tell my how cold or hot is going to be IoI.Some of the other features are alarms, flashlight mode, timer, stopwatch, etc. One of my favorites are the notifications. I always have my cellphone in DND mode, so I used to miss calls and texts very often. Now, the watch starts to vibrate and I know I need to check my phone. I can see my text messages right on the screen and who is calling also. You can't reply back or answer the phone call through the watch, but that is ok with me.The battery lasts several days. I am pretty sure I wore it for a week straight and it was still going before I put it to charge.

    I have been using this watch for about a month now, and I am very impressed. The five star ratings this watch has been receiving this one of the reasons I bought it, and they are very justified. Previously, I had been using the Wyze watch, which I like very much, but it did not have a blood pressure monitoring function which I really wanted to have as I am getting older.

    I had tried a different inexpensive health monitor smart watch previously that was supposed to give blood pressure readings, but most of the health monitor readings were way off and not consistent at all. So that one was sort of a waste of my time/money. The Android app for that watch was also not very useful, and it also had less than a 3-star rating. Remember: The app for a smart watch is something you should always be sure to check BEFORE buying this type of watch.

    This watch uses the Da Fit app which is quite good once you learn to use it, and it seems to work perfectly with this new watch. All of the health functions of this watch seemed to work rather well. The blood pressure monitoring function has to be initiated manually, but that is not a problem for me. It is rather easy to do both on the watch and in the Da Fit app. Of course, the blood pressure function does not exactly replicate the usual cuff blood pressure reading simply because it uses a different type of sensor system. However, it is reasonably close when compared with my very reliable wrist cuff blood pressure monitor. The blood pressure readings also tend to go up and down in accordance with my exertion levels - as expected. I generally take my blood pressure readings 2 or 3 times per day, and the Da Fit app keeps a nice record of those readings for me.

    I also use the Da Fit app to tell the watch to collect my blood pressure readings every half hour, and that works very well. As for sleep monitoring, this watch and the Da Fit app do a pretty nice job. I do like the Wyze watch sleep monitoring function a little bit better, mainly because this watch will think you have woken up, and no longer track your sleep, if you get up and go to the bathroom during the night.

    The watch step counting function seems to be based primarily on your arm movements, so if you're using an exercise bike or a treadmill wear your arm isn't actually moving much while you're exercising it just won't to count that exercise as steps (but shaking hands or stirring a pot does) count). For me this is a minor problem, but if you want to keep an accurate track of your daily step count, you may want to consider using another device.

    As an added bonus, the seller also offered a gift of two addition watch bands (serval different styles to choose from) as alternatives to the standard plastic band - which I appreciated. And last but not least, this watch has been running for a full week before the charge level goes below 'half'. What is not to like about this smart watch for such a reasonable price!

  • ERM-FW
    4.0 out of 5 stars Compact, works, long battery life, a few cons
    Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    Overall pretty good watch. Time keeping, automatic update when synchronized with the smartphone app all work well. Very compact compared to my previous watch. As far as fitness tracking, heart rate and O2 sats are pretty accurate (after the first few readings). Blood pressure readings reads a little low compared to a blood pressure cuff. It would be nice to have a manually entered adjustment field so that it can be more accurate. The Play button does start and stop the music play app on my phone. A few cons: while I'm browsing at my computer in the evening with my left wrist hardly moving, it says I'm sleeping when I'm still awake. So it tends to overreport sleep obtained. The rubber wristband tends to leave my wrist a bit red. So I definitely can't wear this full-time (often taking it off at night which defeats the purpose of sleep tracking). I have found that putting a little bit of olive oil between the wristband and my wrist (the redness being a somewhat common problem with digital watches) seems to provide an irritation barrier. The remote shutter feature doesn't seem to work with the Samsung camera app but I can live without that. I might try to find a leather or metallic band for the watch and see if that helps. For those who say the difference in distance between this app's distance tracker and a phone's distance tracker, the difference may be attributable to not entering the correct value for your steps. Take the phone's distance divided by the number of steps taken to get the average stride length and then enter that into your profile. Now the results should be pretty close.

    Overall it's a nice fitness tracking watch which I would recommend.
